DataElement.preferredDefinition: A piece of tissue removed from an organism for examination, analysis, or propagation._Treatment of a disease by means of exposure of the target or the whole body to radiation. Radiation therapy is often used as part of curative therapy and occasionally as a component of palliative treatment for cancer. Other uses include total body irradiation prior to transplantation.:A quantity of an agent (such as substance or energy) administered, taken, or absorbed at one time._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
